WEBVTT

00:04.854 --> 00:11.279
Welcome to "English in a Minute," where we teach you all about idioms in American English.

00:12.667 --> 00:14.484
Has this ever happened to you?

00:18.083 --> 00:20.172
What was the name of America's first president?

00:20.455 --> 00:22.157
I can't believe you don't remember that.

00:22.235 --> 00:22.715
Come on!

00:22.805 --> 00:23.171
I know.

00:23.556 --> 00:25.159
I know, I've completely drawn a blank.

00:26.074 --> 00:26.947
"Draw a blank?"

00:31.931 --> 00:36.594
She could not remember that George Washington was America's first president...

00:36.750 --> 00:38.811
...because she "drew a blank."

00:39.238 --> 00:41.963
It's another way of saying, "I can't remember something."

00:42.725 --> 00:44.138
There's another meaning, too.

00:44.613 --> 00:49.301
If you're looking for something but can't find it, then you "draw a blank."

00:50.153 --> 00:56.284
In American English, you can use this phrase with friends or in business situations.

00:56.594 --> 00:58.327
And that's "English in a Minute."

